text: Mustafa Mit (born 1 January 1950) is a Turkish politician from the Nationalist Movement Party (MHP), who currently serves as a Member of Parliament for Ankara's second electoral district since 7 June 2015. == Biography == Mustafa Mit was born in Şarkışla, Sivas Province. He completed his primary, secondary and high school education in different parts of Anatolia before graduating from Gazi University Faculty of economics and administrative sciences. == References == Category:1950 births Category:Living people Category:People from Şarkışla Category:Nationalist Movement Party politicians
title: Mustafa Mit
